# IoT-Based Smart Pet Feeder System with Anomaly Detection 🐾

Developed as part of the Embedded Systems course at Istinye University (Computer Engineering Department), this project is a comprehensive Internet of Things (IoT) ecosystem. It automates pet feeding schedules and analyzes consumption data to detect sudden appetite changes or health anomalies using statistical modeling.

## 🚀 Key Features
* **Dual-Core Processing:** Utilizes the high-speed **ESP32** microcontroller, leveraging its built-in Wi-Fi and superior RAM capacity over traditional boards like the Arduino Uno.
* **Real-Time Cloud Integration:** Wirelessly transmits log data asynchronously to the **Firebase Realtime Database**.
* **NTP Time Synchronization:** Uses the `time.h` library to sync with NTP servers for precise UTC+3 time stamping of feeding logs.
* **Anomaly Detection Algorithm:** Implements a 5-element **Circular Buffer** (`float ogun_gecmisi[5]`) in RAM to track a moving average of food consumption and triggers real-time alerts if consumption deviates heavily from the average.

