## 🧠 Engineering Solutions & Debugging

1. **I2C LCD Pin Conflict Resolved:** Initially, the LCD display failed to render characters due to the SDA line being wired to a strapping/boot pin (GPIO 12). Relocating the connection to hardware I2C pins (**GPIO 21** and **GPIO 19**) completely solved the issue.
2. **Baud Rate Mismatch Fixed:** Garbled characters on the Serial Monitor during load cell calibration were resolved by upgrading the firmware communication speed to the industry standard **115200 baud**.
3. **Preventing Mechanical Deadlock:** To stop the servo motor from constantly micro-triggering near the 500g threshold due to minor sensor fluctuations, a hysteresis tolerance was added, setting the lower re-trigger threshold to **450g**.
4. **Eliminating Load Cell Signal Noise:** Structural weight fluctuations caused by environmental vibrations were fully absorbed by designing and mounting a rigid, parallel support apparatus to stabilize the load cell baseline.

